description.plain:
Lakeyah Robinson (born Feb. 28, 2001), known professionally as Lakeyah, is an American rapper from Milwaukee, WI. Lakeyah is signed to Atlanta-based record label Quality Control and has released two studio albums. She was also selected as a member of XXL’s 2021 Freshman Class.

When Lakeyah was 18, she moved to Atlanta to pursue a career in music. She first gained QC label-head Pee’s attention when he heard her remix of JT’s “First Day Out” and she ultimately signed to QC in July of 2020. She’s since released Time’s Up and In Due Time and has seen the most success with her 2020 track “Female Goat (Remix)” featuring City Girls.

The acronym GOAT, meaning “Greatest Of All Time”, has been used by Lakeyah to refer to herself. The term was back then popularized by the veteran rapper LL Cool J, who released an album titled G.O.A.T. (Greatest of All Time) on September 12, 2000.

songs.title: Mind Yo Business

description.plain:
On “Mind Yo Business,” Lakeyah collaborates with fellow Atlanta rapper, Latto, for the first time. Both artists rap about their social standings, tastes, and inclinations toward men who are interested in them. The track also marks Lakeyah’s first release under Motown Records, after she signed a deal with the company. Later on, she revealed the new deal on her Instagram story:

I’m super excited and blessed to also be in business with Motown Records. They’ve always been supportive of my music, and now it’s just on another level.

She also shared through an article how she felt collaborating with Latto:

I got the chance to collab with one of my favorite new-era rap girls! Both the song and the video are fire. I can’t wait for everyone to hear “Mind Yo Business”.

The track was teased three days before its official release date on both of her social media accounts; she said there is a “crazy feature” on it. Later on, she came to disclose on her social media that the “crazy feature” was Latto, despite the track being leaked in its entirety before its official release date.

description.plain:
On “I Look Good”, Lakeyah boasts about her newfound riches and how she can use it to buy fancy items as she seemingly talks about her wonderful figure over a bouncy instrumental.

Lakeyah originally teased the song on her Instagram posts and stories, and it quickly gained popularity after her admirers began producing videos of it on TikTok, prompting her supporters to demand that the music be released. The Milwaukee rapper later uploaded a short video of the track on her Instagram post ahead to its release as her Instagram caption stated.

“I Look Good” Dropping Friday just in time for the summer ! All Bad Bitches to the front line NEOW. DROP A “💅🏽” if you ready!! 💖😍😛💥 #I Look Good

The song was later released accompanied with the video, as we see Lakeyah leading a workout class in an all-pink outfit, later rapping for the camera in a fitness lab, wearing oversized sleek black sunglasses and letting her charisma lead the way as she promised her fans that the track will become a summer anthem.

“Easy” is a remix of American R&B singer DaniLeigh’s homonymous song, which was released on May 20, 2018, for Dani’s album The Plan.

In the song, Lakeyah shows her affection and sexual desires towards her lover and the sex life that they both have together. The track’s lyrical themes are similar to those of Lakeyah’s two other songs, “Wetter” and “Ocean”, which integrate the same album.
